summary: This is a motion filed by the U.S. Attorney's Office to seal a search warrant application related to an ongoing grand jury investigation into Jeffrey Epstein. The motion argues that public disclosure would jeopardize the investigation and notify potential subjects or targets.

persons.name: R. Alexander Acosta
persons.context: He is the United States Attorney who submitted the motion to seal the search warrant application through an Assistant United States Attorney.

events.title: Motion to Seal Search Warrant Application
events.description: The U.S. Attorney's Office files a motion to seal documents related to a search warrant application, citing an ongoing grand jury investigation.

keyFacts: The document is a motion to seal a search warrant application related to the Epstein investigation.
The motion cites an ongoing grand jury investigation as the reason for sealing.
The U.S. Attorney argues public disclosure would jeopardize the investigation and notify potential subjects/targets.
The motion is submitted by U.S. Attorney R. Alexander Acosta through an Assistant U.S. Attorney.
The filing is from the Southern District of Florida, case number 08-8068-LRJ.
